      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Our Zenith X boasts a brighter OLED with dual 50MP rear sensors, while the Apex Pro rivals with a larger AMOLED screen and an impressive triple-camera system including 200MP and macro capabilities. On the inside, the Snapdragon 8 Gen 3 paired with 12GB RAM powers the 120Hz display, whereas the Dimensity 9300 drives the faster 144Hz refresh on 16GB of memory for Apex Pro enthusiasts. We must highlight critical differences: the Zenix's 5000mAh battery and IP68 rating contrast against the Pro's wireless charging and heavier 4800mAh unit, plus both offer fingerprint sensors but differ in location and charging speed. Ultimately, choose the Zenith for its GALA battery life and USB-C encryption features, or pick the Apex Pro for its superior telephoto optics and generous 512GB storage density.",
